		 <h2> About Achievers</h2>
<p class="text-justify">
Achievers Lanka Business School is one of Sri Lanka’s leading providers of professional education and is known for producing outstanding results, inclusive of over 22 World Prizes and 95 National Prizes in just 9 years. We go beyond providing a mere qualification for our students and adorn them with the required skills to excel in the corporate world.</p>
<p class="text-justify">
9 Years ago, Achievers began their journey by introducing a modern learning system that motivates interaction for achieving professional excellence. In doing so, Achievers has been able to procure global recognition as an approved CIMA Global Premium Learning Partner - the highest level of accreditation available from CIMA for course providers, while winning ‘Asia’s Best Business School Leadership’ Award in 2010 and 2012 at the CMO Asia Awards held in Singapore. Achievers Lanka Business School also won a silver award at the SLIM Brand Excellence Awards held in 2012 for excellence in branding. Today, we are strong, with an annual student intake of over 6,000 students.</p>
<p class="text-justify">

“Our vision was to create an exemplary student base, year in, year out - that would comprise a majority, which top corporations would give first preference to. Today, Achievers is one of the very few educational institutes in the island that companies directly approach for prospective employees.”
-Faris Ismail (CEO and Founder)</p>
<p class="text-justify">

Achievers Lanka Business School was established in April of 2006, bringing together five dominant leaders in the CIMA industry with a vision of directly contributing to the corporate world by attracting high caliber students and moulding them to be outstanding professionals. This core team comprising of Ravi Edirisinghe, Jairaj Krishnakumar, Faris Ismail, Senaka Kakiriwaragodage and Azad Hye have been instrumental in bringing Achievers to its current position as a leading institute for CIMA education.</p>
<p class="text-justify">

Achievers is an approved CIMA Global Premium Partner – the highest level of accreditation available and has an experienced lecture panel renowned for producing excellent results. In a short period of six years Achievers has grown rapidly resulting in the opening of branches at Bambalaptiya, Kandy and Gampaha. With an annual student intake of 6,000 we are a major player in the Sri Lankan CIMA arena. We have produced individuals of high quality to the corporate world as at Achievers we not only focus on providing quality education to students but also other extra-curricular activities so that they are groomed to enter the corporate world with an all-round personality.
</p>
<p class="text-justify">
We have won 8 world prizes and 72 Sri Lankan prizes at the CIMA examinations within the past 6 years. In 2012, we had a record 22 prizes at the CIMA examinations. Achievers received the Best Business School Leadership Award at the CMO Awards held in Singapore in 2010 and 2012 and also won a silver award at the SLIM Brand Excellence Awards in 2012.</p>
<p class="text-justify">

Achievers also offers the globally recognized CFA programme (Chartered Financial Analyst) and is the exclusive tuition provider for the Sri Lanka Logistics and Freight Forwarders Association (SLFFA) and the Academy of International Trade and Transport (AITT)for Logistics and International Trade programmes.</p>

